WEBVTT

00:00.953 --> 00:02.703
Previously, on <i>Fringe...</i>

00:02.804 --> 00:04.154
Walter.

00:04.221 --> 00:07.908
I lost the people I loved most,
and I imagine you miss them too,

00:07.992 --> 00:08.909
the people you've
left behind.

00:08.993 --> 00:11.561
Yes, I do.

00:11.612 --> 00:13.763
I will help
you get home.

00:13.831 --> 00:15.332
You okay?

00:15.399 --> 00:16.783
Yeah, I just started
to get another migraine.

00:16.868 --> 00:20.120
<i>I was hoping I wouldn't</i>
<i>need these anymore.</i>

00:25.459 --> 00:27.844
<i>She's not gonna</i>
<i>remember the last two hours.</i>

00:27.912 --> 00:31.598
When she wakes up, she's gonna
have one hell of a headache.

00:31.682 --> 00:33.633
I have come to tell
you something.

00:33.718 --> 00:35.919
<i>Olivia...</i>

00:35.970 --> 00:38.522
Who the hell are you?
How did you know my name?

00:38.589 --> 00:41.691
I have looked
at all possible futures,

00:41.759 --> 00:45.812
and in every one,
the result is the same.

00:45.897 --> 00:48.732
You have to die.

00:54.822 --> 00:55.822
<i>That's him.</i>

00:55.907 --> 00:56.957
<i>Are you sure?</i>

00:57.041 --> 00:58.458
<i>They all look like</i>
<i>the same man.</i>

00:58.543 --> 01:00.777
<i>No, that's the one.</i>

01:00.828 --> 01:03.330
We've been looking at these
people for three years.

01:03.414 --> 01:04.947
Why did they
make contact now?

01:04.998 --> 01:06.049
I don't know.

01:06.116 --> 01:08.284
But he knew my name,
he knew who I was,

01:08.336 --> 01:09.452
and he knew
where to find me.

01:09.503 --> 01:11.638
<i>And then</i>
<i>he just vanished.</i>

01:11.722 --> 01:13.173
What exactly did he say?

01:13.257 --> 01:16.176
He said that he had seen
all possible futures,

01:16.260 --> 01:21.181
and in every one,
I had to die.

01:24.068 --> 01:25.485
<i>I had Astrid run</i>
<i>a sample of his blood.</i>

01:25.570 --> 01:26.820
<i>There was no match</i>
<i>on the DNA,</i>

01:26.904 --> 01:30.974
but she did find antibodies
for the Spanish flu.

01:31.025 --> 01:32.576
The Spanish flu?

01:32.643 --> 01:33.827
Isn't that extinct?

01:33.911 --> 01:36.079
Well, the last recorded
epidemic was in 1919.

01:36.147 --> 01:39.883
<i>Which makes them</i>
<i>a minimum of 91 years old.</i>

01:39.951 --> 01:42.502
I'm going to assign you
a security detail.

01:42.587 --> 01:43.503
<i>I don't think that</i>
<i>that's necessary.</i>

01:43.588 --> 01:44.754
He threatened you.

01:44.822 --> 01:48.341
I'm not sure that's
what he was doing.

01:48.426 --> 01:51.327
I--I think that he was
trying to warn me.

01:51.379 --> 01:53.430
If he approaches
you again,

01:53.497 --> 01:54.497
I expect you to
notify me right away.

01:54.548 --> 01:58.334
Of course.

